## Results & Parameters

- **Canonical field names — TWO layers (verified by reading `models.py` AND `agamemnon_client.py` this session):**
  - Model / YAML field (Pydantic source of truth): `subject` (models.py:38), `assign_to` (models.py:40), `blocked_by` (models.py:41).
  - JSON wire key (REST client serialization): `subject` (agamemnon_client.py:207), `assigneeAgentId` (agamemnon_client.py:211,214), `blockedBy` (agamemnon_client.py:216).
  - The model field `assign_to` is serialized as `assigneeAgentId`; **the two layers differ and must be read separately**. There is NO `assignee_agent_id` field anywhere.
  - Deprecated forms (the only ones that exist): `title` (-> `subject`) and `depends_on` (-> `blocked_by`). There is NO `assigned_to (legacy)` deprecated form — that was a fabricated guess caught by a reviewer.
- **Drift-guard pattern:** first-party-only file list via
  `git ls-files -- '*.md' | awk '!/^(infrastructure|control|provisioning|ci-cd|research|shared|testing)\//'`;
  field-key regex `^[[:space:]]*-?[[:space:]]*(title|depends_on):`;
  exit `0` clean / `1` drift / `2` usage; wire into `just ci`.
- **Submodule dirs in this ecosystem to exclude from first-party scans:** `infrastructure/` `control/` `provisioning/` `ci-cd/` `research/` `shared/` `testing/`.
- **ProjectHephaestus #1553 (`argument-hint` frontmatter, v1.2.0 case):**
  - Named targets: `skills/brainstorm/SKILL.md` (ALREADY compliant — `argument-hint: <idea or feature description>` at line 4; stale audit) and `skills/python-repo-modernization/SKILL.md` (genuinely missing — the only actionable target).
  - Convention (confirmed by reading siblings): `argument-hint` placed immediately after `description`; value describes what the skill operates on. For `python-repo-modernization`: `<path to Python repo to modernize>`.
  - Enforcement: NONE. `grep -rl "argument-hint" tests/` -> no matches; no skill tests under `tests/unit/`. Verification = structural YAML-frontmatter parse (`yaml.safe_load_all`), not a unit test. `argument-hint` is optional/advisory in the Claude Code plugin format (inferred from the absence of any validator, not confirmed against upstream plugin-spec docs).
  - Out-of-scope (deliberately NOT fixed in #1553): ~10 other `skills/*/SKILL.md` also missing `argument-hint`, surfaced by the survey — they belong to the broader audit bundle (split from #1518), one issue per PR.
  - Provenance taken at face value (low risk): the audit timestamp (2026-06-16) and the split-from-#1518 origin.
- **ProjectHephaestus #1449 (subpackage count/listing mismatch in CLAUDE.md, v1.5.0 case — verified-local, ACTUALLY EXECUTED):**
  - Audit framing (strict full-coverage, 2026-06-16): `CLAUDE.md:36` says "20 documented subpackages" but the tree lists only 19, omitting `scripts_lib`. Re-derived live: `find hephaestus -maxdepth 2 -name __init__.py` → 21 paths = 20 subpackages + the package root. The COUNT (20) was CORRECT; only the LISTING was one short. Re-derive count AND listing independently — the audit mis-attributed which side was wrong.
  - Three docs fixed (all carried the same stale inventory): (1) `CLAUDE.md` — added the `scripts_lib/` tree row, alphabetical between `resilience/` and `system/`; (2) `COMPATIBILITY.md:42` — corrected "19 documented subpackages" → "20"; (3) `docs/adr/0001-automation-library-boundary.md:24` — added `scripts_lib` to the library-layer enumeration (`automation` correctly stays excluded as the product layer per the ADR).
  - `README.md` was ALREADY correct (fixed earlier by #1188) — a stale audit target, not re-edited. Always re-read each cited target on disk; do not re-fix what a prior PR already corrected.
  - Scope: `COMPATIBILITY.md` was NOT named by the audit but carried the IDENTICAL stale-inventory defect — folded into the SAME PR as the same-defect-sibling case (in scope), distinct from the broader-survey-surfaces-DIFFERENT-siblings case (out of scope). Distinguishing test: SAME defect on a sibling doc → fold in; a DIFFERENT instance the survey happened to surface → note out-of-scope.
  - Guard: EXTENDED the existing #1188 drift guard `tests/unit/validation/test_readme_subpackage_tree.py` rather than inventing one — added a `CLAUDE_MD` path constant and `test_claude_md_tree_lists_every_subpackage`, reusing the existing `_real_subpackages()` live-disk helper (dirs with `__init__.py`) and the same `f"├── {name}/"` / `f"└── {name}/"` substring matcher the README test uses. A second consumer of the same invariant.
  - TDD: the new test failed RED with exactly `CLAUDE.md directory tree omits subpackage(s): ['scripts_lib']` before the doc edit, passed GREEN after. Full `tests/unit/validation` suite = 784 passed, 16 skipped; `ruff check` clean.
  - Guard scope tradeoff: it asserts tree MEMBERSHIP (the strong invariant — a complete listing implies a correct count for any reader) and deliberately does NOT regex the prose count strings; so the `COMPATIBILITY.md` "20" correction is UNGUARDED by design (YAGNI). A future 21st subpackage would leave prose counts stale while the membership test still passes — an acceptable, documented tradeoff.
  - Verification = `verified-local`: tests run locally (RED→GREEN + full suite green); the PR/CI had NOT merged at capture time — NOT `verified-ci`.
- **ProjectHephaestus #1506 (per-symbol API tables for Stable subpackages, v1.3.0 case — UNVERIFIED, plan only):**
  - Targets: `hephaestus.cli`, `hephaestus.system`, `hephaestus.version` lack per-symbol API tables in `COMPATIBILITY.md`. **No code executed, no tests, no CI** — verification = `unverified`.
  - Stale/under-counted audit: audit claimed `hephaestus.cli.__all__` had 12 symbols; live `hephaestus/cli/__init__.py:22-39` had 16 (audit omitted `DRY_RUN_HELP_CAVEAT`, `add_dry_run_arg`, `add_github_throttle_args`, `configure_github_throttle_from_args`).
  - "Added" version anchors are INFERRED, not verified — labeled "best-effort historical anchors" in the plan. Anchoring method, in priority order: (a) reuse a version already documented for the same symbol in a sibling table (`system.get_system_info` documented `0.3.0` in the top-level table -> reuse `0.3.0` for `format_system_info`); (b) `git log -S <symbol>` to find the introducing commit/PR and map its era to a minor (`emit_json_status`/`add_json_arg` from PR #603 -> `0.6.0`; throttle args from #1520 -> `0.9.0`); (c) default pre-1.0 infrastructure to `0.1.0`. These are the dominant uncertain assumption in the plan.
  - Drift-guard (`api_table_docs.py`, planned): cross-checks table membership against live `__all__` in BOTH directions (missing-from-docs and missing-from-`__all__`) — a hard verifiable invariant. Deliberately does NOT validate the "Added" string. Mirrors `hephaestus/validation/cli_tier_docs.py` (which cross-checks `[project.scripts]` <-> `COMPATIBILITY.md`, wired into `.pre-commit-config.yaml:166` + `pyproject.toml:141`), including console-script registration (`hephaestus-check-api-table-docs`) and pre-commit wiring. Pre-commit `entry` pins `--environment default` because the guard imports the packages via `importlib.import_module` and needs an env where they import cleanly.
  - Reciprocal edit required: registering the new console script means the existing `cli_tier_docs` guard fails unless a "Console-Script Stability Tiers" row is added for it.
  - Reviewer risk areas (do NOT treat the inferred values as authoritative): (1) the "Added" versions are inferred — only the membership invariant is verified; (2) the table-parsing regex (`_TABLE_ROW_RE`, the ``### `package` `` header match) is hand-rolled and may mis-parse if `COMPATIBILITY.md` formatting drifts (backtick style, separator rows) — the live-tree alignment test is the safety net; (3) `test_missing_from_docs_detected` must assert MEMBERSHIP of the expected kind in a result set that ALSO contains many `table-not-found` findings (the tmp doc only has the system table), not equality.
- **ProjectHephaestus #1507 (complete utils + config API tables; FIRST issue to create `api_table_docs.py`, v1.4.0 case — UNVERIFIED, plan only):**
  - Targets: `hephaestus.utils` and `hephaestus.config` per-symbol API tables in `COMPATIBILITY.md` are severely incomplete (majority of `__all__` undocumented). Plan = complete BOTH tables to live `__all__` AND create the bidirectional drift-guard `hephaestus/validation/api_table_docs.py`. **No code executed, no tests, no CI** — verification = `unverified`.
  - Direct follow-on to #1506 — and #1506's guard NEVER LANDED: `test -f hephaestus/validation/api_table_docs.py` -> NO; `COMPATIBILITY.md` still had only logging/config/io/utils tables (no cli/system/version). So #1507 is the FIRST issue to actually create the guard. A captured plan (the v1.3.0 skill note) is NOT evidence the work shipped — re-verify on disk.
  - Audit counts were ACCURATE this time (contrast #1506, which was stale/under-counted): live `hephaestus.utils.__all__`=14 (table listed 5), `hephaestus.config.__all__`=13 (table listed 5), via `python3 -c "import hephaestus.utils as m; print(len(m.__all__)); print(sorted(m.__all__))"`. Re-derive every issue — the result varies.
  - Deprecated-member-still-needs-a-row: `retry_with_jitter` was in `COMPATIBILITY.md:193` deprecation PROSE but absent from the utils table; it is still in `__all__`, so the completed table needs a row flagged deprecated, matching the `get_config_value` precedent at `COMPATIBILITY.md:210`. Membership is independent of deprecation status.
  - "Added" anchors (best-effort, NOT facts; via `git log -S <symbol> --reverse -- hephaestus/`): `get_repo_root` from an early src-merge commit; `validate_config` from the initial impl commit `50c5eca4`; `parse_pixi_toml`/`dep_sync` family from `056462a0` (config port). Pre-1.0 infra with no clearer anchor -> `0.1.0`. The guard does NOT assert these.
  - The `api_table_docs.py` guard validates ONLY membership (both directions: `missing-from-docs` + `missing-from-all`), mirrors `cli_tier_docs.py` exactly, and trips the sibling `cli_tier_docs` guard via the new console script `hephaestus-check-api-table-docs` unless a reciprocal `| hephaestus-check-api-table-docs | Internal | ... |` Console-Script Stability Tiers row is added.
- **ProjectHephaestus #1456 (bare-`gh`-subprocess audit on `severity_label.py`, v1.6.0 case — DIAGNOSIS verified-local; allowlist-comment edit PLAN ONLY):**
  - Audit finding: "`github/severity_label.py:76` bypasses the `gh` circuit breaker with a bare `subprocess.run`." STALE on TWO axes — the source was already remediated AND a test guard already enforces the invariant.
  - Source remediated by PR #1520 / commit `940ea102` (after the 2026-06-16 audit): `grep -nE "subprocess" hephaestus/github/severity_label.py` returns nothing; `_gh()` at lines 80-82 delegates to `gh_call`. The cited "line 76" is `return candidate` inside `parse_severity`, not a subprocess call — the audit was wrong on the line too.
  - Existing guard (already enforces the invariant): `tests/unit/github/test_no_raw_gh_subprocess.py` — `_TARGETS = (fleet_sync.py, severity_label.py)` at lines 12-15; the AST detector at lines 19-127 handles subprocess aliases (`import subprocess as sp`), `from subprocess import run`, command-in-variable (assignment tracking), list concatenation (`['gh'] + [...]` BinOp), and `shell=True` string forms (shlex.split); the assertion `test_target_modules_do_not_run_gh_via_subprocess` is at line 130.
  - Scoped test result: `pixi run pytest tests/unit/github/test_no_raw_gh_subprocess.py` → `8 passed`. The `FAIL Required test coverage of 83.0% not reached` line is the GLOBAL coverage gate on a single-file run, NOT a test failure.
  - Sanctioned exceptions deliberately NOT in `_TARGETS` (would wrongly fail CI if blanket-added): `tidy.py:168,180` (interactive `gh tidy`) and `rate_limit.py:255-256` (the `gh api rate_limit` reset probe) — documented exceptions per the `hephaestus/github/client.py` docstring; they cannot re-enter `gh_call`.
  - Corrected precedent path: the mirror pattern is `tests/unit/validation/test_automation_boundary.py` (confirmed via `ls`), NOT `tests/unit/test_automation_boundary.py` (cited 4× in the first plan; does not exist there).
  - Correct disposition: CLOSE the issue with both pieces of evidence (source fixed + guard exists). The ONLY defensible code edit — a COMMENT on `_TARGETS` documenting why the allowlist is curated — was PLANNED ONLY, never written to disk, no CI. The first plan's NEW guard `tests/unit/github/test_no_bare_gh_subprocess.py` (a strictly-weaker inline-list-literal-only duplicate) earned a NOGO (Grade D) and was removed entirely.
