## v1.6.0 (2026-06-30)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1456 (audit: "github/severity_label.py:76 bypasses the gh circuit breaker with a bare subprocess.run") — DIAGNOSIS verified-local; the proposed allowlist-documenting comment edit was plan-only
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Added the "search-for-an-existing-guard-before-authoring-one" case, which EXTENDS the skill's existing already-remediated → pivot-to-a-drift-guard advice (step 5) with a critical caveat: the pivot itself can cause a DRY/YAGNI violation unless you grep for an existing guard FIRST.
- New axis: an audit finding can be stale on TWO axes at once — the SOURCE was already remediated (PR #1520 / 940ea102) AND a TEST GUARD already enforces it (`tests/unit/github/test_no_raw_gh_subprocess.py` lists `severity_label.py` in `_TARGETS:14`). A proposed NEW guard `test_no_bare_gh_subprocess.py` earned a NOGO (Grade D) as a strictly-weaker duplicate.
- New rule: compare a proposed detector's coverage against the existing one before claiming it adds value; a strictly-weaker detector is a coverage-implying regression.
- New rule: a curated `_TARGETS`/allowlist is intentional — un-listed siblings (`tidy.py:168,180`, `rate_limit.py:255-256`) are DOCUMENTED SANCTIONED `gh_call` exceptions per `client.py`; document why the allowlist is curated, don't blanket-extend.
- New verification caveat: a `FAIL Required test coverage of N% not reached` line on a scoped pytest run is the GLOBAL coverage gate, NOT a test failure — read the `N passed` summary line.
- New rule: verify cited precedent PATHS exist (`ls`) before relying on them — the first plan cited the non-existent `tests/unit/test_automation_boundary.py`; the real path is `tests/unit/validation/test_automation_boundary.py`.
- Added 5 Failed Attempts rows and a Results & Parameters subsection for #1456.

### Why
The skill's own recommended pivot (already-remediated target → author a drift-guard) backfired: ProjectHephaestus issue #1456's first plan created a NEW guard that duplicated an existing one and got a NOGO. The amendment folds in the missing precondition — search for an existing guard enforcing the same invariant before writing one — plus the detector-coverage, curated-allowlist, coverage-gate-FAIL, and verify-precedent-path sub-lessons. Diagnosis steps were run against the live ProjectHephaestus tree (verified-local); the optional allowlist-comment edit was never written to disk (plan-only).

### Previous version (v1.5.0) snapshot

````markdown
