## v1.5.0 (2026-06-30)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1449 implementation (CLAUDE.md subpackage count/listing mismatch) — ACTUALLY EXECUTED, verified-local
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Added the FIRST verified-local (actually-shipped) case to a skill whose #1506/#1507 entries were all plan-only/unverified.
- New "count is correct, listing is short" sub-case: an audit can frame a defect as "count says X, listing shows X-1" when in fact the COUNT is correct and only the LISTING is one short — re-derive both independently.
- New pattern: fold a same-defect SIBLING doc into scope (the audit named CLAUDE.md + ADR-0001; COMPATIBILITY.md had the identical stale inventory count and was correctly fixed in the same PR as the same defect, not scope creep).
- Reinforced "extend the existing guard, don't invent one": the #1188 README-tree drift guard `tests/unit/validation/test_readme_subpackage_tree.py` was extended to also cover CLAUDE.md by reusing its `_real_subpackages()` live-disk helper — a second consumer of the same invariant.
- Confirmed the membership-guard-not-count-guard tradeoff in practice: the guard asserts tree membership (the strong invariant) and deliberately does NOT regex the prose count strings; the count corrections in CLAUDE.md/COMPATIBILITY.md remain unguarded by design (YAGNI).

### Why
Previous entries (v1.3.0 #1506, v1.4.0 #1507) documented PLANS that were never executed. This session executed an audit remediation end-to-end with RED→GREEN TDD and a green validation suite, validating the skill's core workflow against reality for the first time.

